  "texts": [
    "This approach not only avoids the complicated mathematical derivations but also offers an opportunity to deal with mathematically intractable problems.",
    "Third, the fast inference speed of AI facilitates its online deployment.",
    "However, the AI-driven methods undergo some inherent limitations, such as high training samples requirements and limited interpretability, and the optimality of solutions cannot be guaranteed.",
    "Moreover, the AI model should be carefully chosen to match the underlying problem structure [216].",
    "For instance, DRL has been widely leveraged to deal with the multistep decision problems, while FL is more suitable for handling the distributed optimization problems."
  ]
}